def: Rendered dense or compact, as by evaporation; inspissated;thickened. [R.]The spissated juice of the poppy. Bp. Warburton.
Capable of being enjoyed or of giving joy; yielding enjoyment.Milton.

The widening and duplication, triplication, etc., of spectrallines when the radiations emanate in a strong magnetic field, firstobserved in 1896 by P. Zeeman, a Dutch physicist, and regarded as animportant confirmation of the electromagnetic theory of light.
By way of derision or mockery.
A rare metallic element of the boron-aluminium group, found ingadolinite and other rare minerals, and extracted as a dark graypowder. Symbol Y. Atomic weight, 89. [Written also ittrium.]
Inclined or tending to remonstrate; expostulatory; urgingreasons in opposition to something.

On a painting, and sometimes in a bas-relief, mosaic picture,or the like, that part of the scene represented, which is nearest tothe spectator, and therefore occupies the lowest part of the work ofart itself. Cf. Distance, n., 6.
A genus of hydroids having large, naked, flowerlike hydranthsat the summits of long, slender, usually simple, stems. Thegonophores are small, and form clusters at the bases of the outertentacles.
A substance allied to alkali albumin and to mucin, present insemen, to which it is said to impart the mucilaginous character.
